videos.description: Rae Burrell maneuvers around the Wildcats' defense and drains the 3-pointer to pull the Lady Volunteers within four.

videos.description: The crowd goes in a frenzy as Alexus Dye drains the layup on one end of the floor while Rae Burrell elevates for the big-time block on the other.

videos.description: Jazmine Massengill knocks down the clutch layup to seal the victory and send Kentucky to the SEC Tournament championship game.

videos.headline: Jazmine Massengill drives and drains the clutch layup for Kentucky

videos.description: Rhyne Howard says that after nine straight wins Kentucky is poised to give South Carolina all it can handle in the SEC Tournament Championship Game.
videos.headline: Howard says UK has the momentum required to win title

videos.description: With Rhyne Howard leading the way, Kentucky buries 12 of 24 three-pointers to take down Tennessee, 83-74, and advance to the SEC Tournament final.
videos.headline: 3-point barrage pushes 7-seed UK past 3-seed UT
